HOWTOs:

- Prerequisite: Intel DAAL's libraries/headers must be installed. In what follows, they are installed in /home/g.racic/sync/intel
https://software.intel.com/content/www/us/en/develop/tools/oneapi/base-toolkit/download.html

- To create a dynamic library libonedal_wrapper.so which statically links Intel DAAL's libraries:
g++ -I/home/g.racic/sync/intel/oneapi/dal/latest/include -DONEAPI_DAAL_USE_MKL_GPU_GEMM -Wl,--start-group -lpthread -ldl -lOpenCL -Wl,--end-group -c -fpic *.cc *.cc
g++ -shared -o libonedal_wrapper.so *.o -L/home/g.racic/sync/intel/oneapi/dal/latest/lib/intel64 -l:libonedal_core.a -l:libonedal_sequential.a

- To compile the test with the dynamic library:
g++ -L/home/g.racic/sync/inteldaalwrapper -I/home/g.racic/sync/intel/oneapi/dal/latest/include -I/home/g.racic/sync/inteldaalwrapper -Wall -o test test_wrapper.cc -lonedal_wrapper -lpthread -ldl
LD_LIBRARY_PATH=/home/g.racic/sync/inteldaalwrapper:$LD_LIBRARY_PATH
